==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Netsuke
<hw>Net"su*ke</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Jap.]</ety>
<def>In Japanese costume and decorative art, a small object carved in
wood, ivory, bone, or horn, or wrought in metal, and pierced with holes
for cords by which it is connected, for convenience, with the inro, the
smoking pouch (tabako-ire), and similar objects carried in the girdle.
It is now much used on purses sold in Europe and America.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>Webster 1913 Suppl.</source>]</p>

